getEntriesByDate

public java.util.Map<java.lang.Object,java.util.List<ViewEntryWrapper>> getEntriesByDate()
Get entries only based on a passed date. createDateRangeFromStartDate handles getting just selected date or all from selected date.

If there are no entries after the selected date, just abort.

Otherwise, load count entries into the wrapper. If there are fewer entries than count in the view, set endOfView to true. Also, recalculate the available pages.

Returns:
Map of KeyDateEntryWrappers to display to the user

getEntriesByCustomer

public java.util.Map<java.lang.Object,java.util.List<ViewEntryWrapper>> getEntriesByCustomer()
Get entries based on customer and date (date is always set). If "Restrict to Date" is selected on the browser (isSingleCat=true), then only get entries for the selected date, otherwise for a year into the future.

If isSingleCat and there are none that match, just abort.

Otherwise, get the entries for selected customer starting from selected date. If there are none after selected date, also just abort.

Otherwise, load count entries into the wrapper. If there are fewer entries than count in the view, set endOfView to true. Also, recalculate the available pages.

Returns:
of KeyDateEntryWrappers to display to the user

createDateRangeFromStartDate

private org.openntf.domino.DateRange createDateRangeFromStartDate()
Creates a DateRange based on the start date, extending either a single day or a month. The DateRange is then used to restrict the wrapper's contents.

Returns:
DateRange either a single day (if isSingleCat()) or five years
